The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks to replace traditional optimization algorithms for sparse estimation problems. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG), as the paper proposes a learning-based approach to solving optimization problems. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Bayesian techniques (cs.IT) and majorization-minimization algorithms (cs.NA) for promoting sparsity. The paper also mentions applications in direction-of-arrival (DOA) and 3D geometry recovery problems (cs.SY, cs.CV).
